{"lemma":"عَدَدَيْ","slug":"عَدَدَيْ","root":"ع.د.د","root_slug":"ع-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَدَد","root":"عدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28287","n28288"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"number"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"numeral"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"years of life"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"multitude, crowd"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"family"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to count off, to enumerate","examples":[{"text":"Quran\nٱَلَّذِي جَمَعَ مَالًا وَعَدَّدَهُ\nallaḏī jamaʕa mālan waʕaddadahu"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wail, to lament (of women, for the dead)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to multiply, make numerous"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.dad/","/ʕad.da.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28287","headword_ar":"عَدَدٌ","root":"Ed","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~ahu","text_ar":"عَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he numbered it; ” as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadiydN","text_ar":"عَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) [originally] What is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"numbered, counted, reckoned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"computed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K: [in the CK, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is inadvertently omitted after the explanation of this meaning:]) [and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadiydN","text_ar":"عَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. therewith [in this sense, as will be seen in what follows]; (A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a quantity composed of units;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore not [properly] applicable to one; but accord. to the grammarians, one belongs to the predicament of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEadadu","text_ar":"العَدَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is the root thereof, and because it implies quantity, for when it is said “ How many hast thou? ” it is as proper to answer “ One ” as it is to answer “ Three ” &c.: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^akovara Eadiydahumo","text_ar":"مَا اَكْثَرَ عَدِيدَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadadahumo","text_ar":"عَدَدَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How great is their number!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) Zj says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadadN","text_ar":"عَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in the sense of an inf. n.; as in the phrase in the Kur [xviii. 10],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siniyna EadadFA","text_ar":"سِنِينَ عَدَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": but many say that it is in this instance used in its proper sense, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoduwdapF","text_ar":"مَعْدُودَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"numbered"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and is made masc. because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siniyn","text_ar":"سِنِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaAm","text_ar":"اَعْوَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^aHoSaY","text_ar":"وَاَحْصَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~a $aYo'K EadadFA","text_ar":"كُلَّ شَىْءٍ عَدَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxii. last verse], it is used in its proper sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoduwdFA","text_ar":"مَعْدُودًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is put in the accus. case as a denotative of state; or it is used in this case as an inf. n. (IAth, O.) ―         -b2-  It signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"years of"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life, which one numbers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K. [In the CK, after the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlEadadu AlmEduwdu","text_ar":"وَالعَدَدُ المعدُودُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"should be inserted.]) Hence the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raq~a Eadaduhu","text_ar":"رَقَّ عَدَدُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The years of his life, which he numbered, became few, the greater part having passed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n28288","headword_ar":"عِدَدٌ","root":"Ed","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}